  "prompt": "What is the best movie that didn't win an Oscar?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" movie that didn't win an Oscar is subjective and depends on personal taste, but there are several critically acclaimed and beloved films that were overlooked by the Academy. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)**  \n   - Despite being widely regarded as one of the greatest films of all time, it was nominated for seven Oscars but won none. It lost to \"Forrest Gump\" in most categories.\n\n2. **\"Citizen Kane\" (1941)**  \n   - Often cited as the greatest film ever made, it won only one Oscar (Best Original Screenplay) and lost Best Picture to \"How Green Was My Valley.\"\n\n3. **\"2001: A Space Odyssey\" (1968)**  \n   - Stanley Kubrick's groundbreaking sci-fi masterpiece won only one Oscar (for Visual Effects) and wasn't even nominated for Best Picture.\n\n4. **\"Do the Right Thing\" (1989)**  \n   - Spike Lee's powerful exploration of racial tension was snubbed for Best Picture and Best Director nominations, despite its cultural impact.\n\n5. **\"The Social Network\" (2010)**  \n   - While it won three Oscars (including Best Adapted Screenplay), it lost Best Picture to \"The King's Speech,\" a decision many critics and audiences still debate.\n\n6. **\"Goodfellas\" (1990)**  \n   - Martin Scorsese's iconic mob film lost Best Picture to \"Dances with Wolves,\" a decision that remains controversial among film enthusiasts.\n\n7. **\"Fight Club\" (1999)**  \n   - Though it didn't receive any Oscar nominations, it has since become a cult classic and is widely regarded as a groundbreaking film.\n\n8. **\"The Wizard of Oz\" (1939)**  \n   - While it won two Oscars (including Best Original Song), it lost Best Picture to \"Gone with the Wind.\"\n\n9. **\"Blade Runner\" (1982)**  \n   - Ridley Scott's visionary sci-fi film was initially overlooked by the Oscars but has since gained a massive following and critical reappraisal.\n\n10. **\"Pulp Fiction\" (1994)**  \n   - Quentin Tarantino's influential film won Best Original Screenplay but lost Best Picture to \"Forrest Gump.\"\n\nEach of these films has left an indelible mark on cinema, even if they didn't take home the top prize. The Oscars don't always reflect the enduring legacy or cultural impact of a film, and many of these are now considered classics despite their lack of awards.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
